const ItemListContainer = () => { return ( <>

If anyone asks where I am, I've left the country. So, Jonathan, how was the pull-out? No... no El, you're not the monster. You saved me. Do you understand? You saved me. Why do we even need weapons anyway? We have her. I need my paddles! You are such a nerd. No wonder you only hang out with boys.

Oh... candy, leftovers, Eggo's... she really likes Eggo's. Why do we even need weapons anyway? We have her. Um, I'm happy you're home. We never would've upset you if we knew you had superpowers. I need my paddles! Um, I'm happy you're home. It’s about the shadow monster, isn’t it?

Just wait till we tell Will that Jennifer Hayes was crying at his funeral. Um, I'm happy you're home. You are such a nerd. No wonder you only hang out with boys. Mornings are for coffee and contemplation. You’re going to take out the demigorgon with a slingshot?

Nancy, seriously, you're gonna be so cool now, it's ridiculous. You act like you want me to be your friend and then you treat me like garbage. You’re going to be home by 8, listening to the Talking Heads and reading Vonnegut or something. That sounds like a nice night.

) } export default ItemListContainer
